 *   I1: Bytes that didn't come from media are 0xFF + confidence 0 + RECONSTRUCTED flag.
 *   I2: Probabilistic corrections check uniqueness across all candidates.
 *   I3: passes[].crc_ok / .quality are honored — verified reads dominate.
 *   I4: Counters use uint32_t (or size_t) to match input scale.
 *   I5: confidence_map[] is updated for every output[] write.
 *
